Gen AI (short for Generative Artificial Intelligence) is a type of AI that can create new, original content â€” not just analyze or predict based on existing data.

Itâ€™s called â€œgenerativeâ€ because it generates text, images, music, code, videos, and more.

ğŸ§  Definition
--------------
Generative AI is a branch of artificial intelligence that uses machine learning models (especially large language models or diffusion models) to produce new data similar to what it was trained on.

For example:

You give it a prompt â†’ â€œWrite a poem about the moon.â€
â†’ It creates a poem that has never existed before.

Or you say â†’ â€œDraw a futuristic city.â€
â†’ It creates an image from scratch.

âš™ï¸ How It Works
----------------
Generative AI is powered by neural networks, trained on vast amounts of data (text, images, audio, etc.).
It learns patterns, relationships, and structures â€” then uses that knowledge to produce realistic outputs.

Model Type	What It Generates	Examples
Large Language Models (LLMs)	Text, code, summaries, chat	ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude
Diffusion Models	Images, videos, art	DALLÂ·E, Midjourney, Stable Diffusion
Audio Models	Music, voice, sound effects	Suno, ElevenLabs, OpenAI Voice
Multimodal Models	Combine text, image, video understanding	GPT-4, Gemini 1.5, Claude 3.5

